  m_Name: Module_4_Set_Q2
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: 'Tomas is programming an app to help people find their way in his city.
    He programs every possible route from the university auditorium to the museum.

    Which
    of the following is Tomas likely using?'
  questionId: 1
  answers:
  - Machine learning
  - Programmable computing
  - Heuristic computing
  - Deep learning
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 01000000
  correctMessage: Programmable computing requires Tomas to manually enter every possible
    route in a database. Machine learning only requires him to provide city locations;
    it can find routes, by itself, as needed.
  incorrectMessage: Programmable computing requires Tomas to manually enter every
    possible route in a database. Machine learning only requires him to provide city
    locations; it can find routes, by itself, as needed.
